1. Tony's mental toughness - Khabib's never fought anyone with the mental toughness/stamina/endurance/pace that Tony has.
2. Embracing the ground position - Like EVERY one of Khabib's opponents, Tony won't freak out like a deer in the headlights when he's taken down. He's not going to spend all the energy in the world trying to get back up only to be taken right back down...Tony will embrace the ground (see Bravo's quote on this on JRE).

snippet.textDisplay:
I know Khabib is a monster in the grappling department, but i'm surprised how nobody ever reported Tony is an NCAA wrestler of elite level.
We tend to forget it, because he wins so many fights with just striking.
But he CAN give khabib a run for his money by avoiding takedowns, or maybe even escaping an unfavorable position. Certainly, he cannot reverse a takedown into a submission, like he has done with other guys, but point is, TONY IS NOT CONOR.
We can't go by the usual "in standup one has the advantage, when on the ground it's over".
For the FIRST TIME, it's more complicated than that.
Tony might be the better wrestler Khabib has ever faced, but he's ALSO an incredibly versatile, unpredictable and dangerous striker.
That's why he's got the better chance anybody has had up until now: he's a much better striker, WHILE ALSO being theorically able to resist takedowns better than any other opponent the dagestani has fought until now

snippet.textDisplay: What makes Tony’s fighting style unique, are three things: 1) his natural abilities-toughness (can take a hit and recover), his long arms, huge hands, and his unbelievable cardio 2) his fighting style(s) (he has many), makes it hard to train for or anticipate, 3) his attitude-this I believe is what will separate him from all before him, at least from Michael Johnson onward. All the fighters who came after Johnson, began to fear Khabib’s ground and pound. They changed how they naturally fought, to protect against that one thing. Tony is not going to change once the octagon gate shuts...and Khabib knows that Tony is crazy. Lastly, Tony has had 5 Years to study Khabib. This is an advantage for Tony (cause Khabib doesn’t vary his fighting style), and a disadvantage for Khabib (Tony’s style is continually evolving).
